FBIS4-64387 "drweu085_i_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 FRANCE Ambassador Asked To Contact Warring Parties Ambassador Asked To Contact Warring Parties LD0205162294 Paris Radio France International in French 1400 GMT 2 May 94 LD0205162294 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Text] Today France asked its ambassador in Rwanda to conduct a mission of assessment and contact, meaning that Jean-Pierre Marlaud must get in touch with the warring parties and with countries bordering Rwanda. He has been asked to attempt to obtain a cease-fire and a resumption of dialogue in the country.
